# Data Safety Rules

The user owns all data and environments. The AI is an assistant — not an operator.

## NEVER do this without explicit user approval

- NEVER execute any write/mutate operation on any database (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, ALTER, DROP, TRUNCATE)
- NEVER run commands on the VPS via SSH that modify state (docker exec with SQL, ALTER USER, restart containers, etc.)
- NEVER open SSH tunnels without telling the user first
- NEVER delete or modify checkpoints, sessions, user data, or any persisted state
- NEVER run `docker exec ... psql` with mutating SQL
- NEVER assume "this is obviously safe to do" — always ask first

## Always do this

- ALWAYS show the exact command/SQL and explain what it will do BEFORE running it
- ALWAYS wait for explicit "yes" / "go ahead" from the user before executing anything that modifies data
- For read-only queries (SELECT, status checks) — these are fine without approval
- If unsure whether an operation is destructive — ask

## Environments

- Local, Dev (VPS), Prod (VPS) are all real environments with real user data
- Treat all three with the same care — dev and prod are not sandboxes
